&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So now whenever we activate this style and add grid-backdrop-enabled to html, the grid will show up as a backdrop against the transparent body and we can use it to check for alignment issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/grid-backdrop.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can always adjust the SVG to tweak the appearance of the grid. Here is a slightly adapted one which highlights 5px, 10px, 50px and 100px boundaries with different colors:&lt;/p&gt;
